- id: REQ-<scope>-<NNN>
  type: quality_attribute
  # Single-target form (most NFRs):
  statement: |
    The <ELEMENT 1: system or subsystem, named specifically>
    shall <ELEMENT 2: response or behaviour being measured>
    in <ELEMENT 3: metric with unit>
    at <ELEMENT 4: target at correct statistical level — e.g. p95, not mean>
    under <ELEMENT 5: condition — load + environment + measurement point>.
  # Multi-level form (Planguage) — replace `statement` with `planguage` block
  # when the right target is a range:
  # planguage:
  #   scale:   "<what is being measured>"
  #   meter:   "<how, over what window; exclusions>"
  #   fail:    "<below which the system is in violation>"
  #   goal:    "<committed target>"
  #   stretch: "<desirable, not committed>"
  #   wish:    "<aspirational>"
  rationale: |
    <why this target; what trade-off; derivation from parent NFR if applicable>
  derived_from:
    - <upstream NFR / inherited regulatory constraint / parent commitment>
